  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong></p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat, and boil a full kettle</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>bacon lardons </strong>and <strong>sliced mushrooms </strong>and cook for 8-10 min or until the bacon is cooked through and crisp, then transfer to a plate (reserve the pan for later!) – these are your <strong>crispy lardons & mushrooms</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1615291428833-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1615291428833-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1615291428833-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1615291428833-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1615291428833-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>linguine </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the linguine for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>linguine</strong>, reserving a cup of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1615291439612-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1615291439612-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1615291439612-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1615291439612-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1615291439612-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the linguine is cooking, peel and roughly chop the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve the<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and add 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[80ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse the<strong> cannellini beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1615291451424-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1615291451424-x400.jpg",
