          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1615291462807-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan with any cooking juices and add 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]<strong> </span>olive oil </strong>to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>cannellini beans </strong>and cook for 2-3 min until the beans are starting to colour</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken stock </strong>and cook for 1-2 min further</p><p>Transfer to a <strong>food processor</strong> (reserving the pan) and blitz until smooth – this is your <strong>creamy bean sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1615291483640-x200.jpg",
